{"title_page": "Yusuke Ueda", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name= Yusuke Ueda\n|fullname=\n|birth_date= 20 October 1990\n|birth_place= [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]\n|youthclubs1= [https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/\u52a0\u85e4\u5b66\u5712\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u6821 Katoh Gakuen High School]\n|college1= [[Kibi International University]] \n|years1= 2013\u20132014<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140101112155/http://www.spcom.co.jp/sports/football/info/2013/index20131217ueda.html \u4e0a\u7530 \u7950\u8f14\u9078\u624b\u3001\u9000\u56e3\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b] \u4f50\u5ddd\u5370\u5237SC (Archived)</ref>\n|clubs1= [[SP Kyoto FC]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130421025246/http://www.spcom.co.jp/sports/football/info/2013/index20130205-19.html \u4e0a\u7530\u7950\u8f14\u9078\u624b\u3001\u5409\u5099\u56fd\u969b\u5927\u5b66\u304b\u3089\u65b0\u52a0\u5165] \u4f50\u5ddd\u5370\u5237SC (Archived)</ref>\n|years2= 2014\n|clubs2= [[Albirex Niigata Singapore FC]]\n|caps2= 7\n|goals2= 0\n|years3= 2014\n|clubs3= [[Albirex Niigata Phnom Penh FC]]\n|years4= 2016\u2013\n|clubs4= [[Wollongong Olympic FC]]\n|caps4= 54\n|goals4= 43\n}}\n\n'''Yusuke Ueda''' ([[Japanese language|Japanese]]: \u4e0a\u7530\u7950\u8f14, ''Ueda Yusuke'', born 20 October 1990 in [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]) is a [[Japan]]ese footballer who currently plays for [[Wollongong Olympic FC|Wollongong Olympic]] of the Australian [[Illawarra Premier League]] as of 2016.\n\n==Career==\n===Singapore===\nEngaged in a transfer to [[Albirex Niigata Singapore FC|Albirex Niigata S]] of the [[Singapore Premier League]] for 2014.<ref>[http://www.albirex.com.sg/archives/4396/ Contract with Yusuke Ueda] Albirex Niigata Singapore</ref>\n\n===Cambodia===\nFinalized a switch to Albirex Niigata subsidiary [[Albirex Niigata Phnom Penh FC|Albirex Niigata Phnom Penh]] for the rest of 2014.<ref>[http://www.albirex.com.sg/archives/9909/ Announcement of Ueda\u2019s transfer] Albirex Niigata Singapore</ref>\n\n===Australia===\nPracticing with a Sydney [[National Premier Leagues]] side in winter 2015,<ref>[http://goshufootballers.com/2015/11/post.html \uff08\u30aa\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30ea\u30a2\uff09\u4e0a\u7530\u7950\u8f14\uff08\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\uff09] \u8c6a\u5dde\u30d5\u30c3\u30c8\u30dc\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba</ref> Ueda was announced as a [[Wollongong Olympic FC|Wollongong Olympic]] athlete in 2016, with his contract renewed for the 2017<ref>[http://goshufootballers.com/2016/09/post.html \uff08\u30aa\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30ea\u30a2\uff09\u5951\u7d04\u66f4\u65b0\uff08\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\uff09] \u8c6a\u5dde\u30d5\u30c3\u30c8\u30dc\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba</ref> and 2018<ref>[http://goshufootballers.com/2017/12/post-2ed9.html \uff08\u30aa\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30ea\u30a2\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\uff09\u5951\u7d04\u66f4\u65b0\u306e\u69d8\u5b50] \u8c6a\u5dde\u30d5\u30c3\u30c8\u30dc\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba</ref> seasons, producing hat-tricks in a 4-1 crushing of [[Port Kembla FC|Port Kembla]]<ref>[https://www.illawarramercury.com.au/story/4751408/ueda-stars-as-olympic-take-lead-in-title-race/ Ueda stars as Olympic take the lead in title race] Illawarra Mercury</ref> as well in a 3-0 trouncing of [[Albion Park White Eagles]]<ref>[http://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?client=1-4704-0-0-0&sID=352503&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=57862050 UEDA STRIKES GOLD FOR OLYMPIC] Football South Coast - SportsTG</ref> during 2017, also producing a brace to overpower [[Cringila Lions FC|Cringila Lions]] 2-0 on the 28th of April 2018.<ref>[http://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?client=0-4704-0-0-0&sID=352503&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=61996268 UEDA DOUBLE DOWNS CRINGILA] Football South Coast - SportsTG</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.illawarramercury.com.au/story/5383538/ueda-inspires-olympic-success/ Ueda inspires Olympic success] \n* [https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/\u4e0a\u7530\u7950\u8f14 Japanese wikipedia Page] \n* [http://www.footballsouthcoast.com/team_info.cgi?action=PSTATS&pID=201355608&client=0-4704-62817-401227-14753897 SportsTG Profile] \n* [https://gh.soccerway.com/players/yusuke-ueda/331125/ at Soccerway]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ueda, Yusuke}}\n[[Category:Association football people from Shizuoka Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Albirex Niigata Singapore FC players]]\n[[Category:Singapore Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Kibi International University alumni]]\n[[Category:SP Kyoto FC players]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name= Yusuke Ueda\n|fullname=\n|birth_date= 20 October 1990\n|birth_place= [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]\n|youthclubs1= [https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/\u52a0\u85e4\u5b66\u5712\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u6821 Katoh Gakuen High School]\n|college1= [[Kibi International University]] \n|years1= 2013\u20132014<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140101112155/http://www.spcom.co.jp/sports/football/info/2013/index20131217ueda.html \u4e0a\u7530 \u7950\u8f14\u9078\u624b\u3001\u9000\u56e3\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b] \u4f50\u5ddd\u5370\u5237SC (Archived)</ref>\n|clubs1= [[SP Kyoto FC]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130421025246/http://www.spcom.co.jp/sports/football/info/2013/index20130205-19.html \u4e0a\u7530\u7950\u8f14\u9078\u624b\u3001\u5409\u5099\u56fd\u969b\u5927\u5b66\u304b\u3089\u65b0\u52a0\u5165] \u4f50\u5ddd\u5370\u5237SC (Archived)</ref>\n|years2= 2014\n|clubs2= [[Albirex Niigata Singapore FC]]\n|caps2= 7\n|goals2= 0\n|years3= 2014\n|clubs3= [[Albirex Niigata Phnom Penh FC]]\n|years4= 2016\u2013\n|clubs4= [[Wollongong Olympic FC]]\n|